repository-code: 'https://github.com/jairomelo/ai-batch-data-extraction'
abstract: >-
  This is an experiment to explore the possibilities for a
  pipeline to extract and structure data from archival or
  printed sources, using AI in combination with traditional
  scripting to reduce the number of tokens, prepare the
  attachments for easy parsing for the models.


  The structure is based on OpenAI-compatible APIs, so it's
  possible to use any common provider, such as OpenAI,
  Anthropic, Meta, etc., and also custom providers such as
  universities or research centers, or can even run local
  small models without compromising the data with external
  services.


  This pipeline is a simple exercise with a low level of
  reproducibility, mostly a personal project, but any
  suggestions are always welcome, as well as any
  implementation beyond this project.
keywords:
